  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: it is possible to request invalid amount with symbols, letters etc (i.e. `/request ETH 0,1Aaa` will successfully proceed to 1-1 chat). If user uses `/send` and enter invalid amount - this value is sent to wallet screen and is validated by the wallet. Expected, that user cannot proceed to Wallet screen if he typed wrong (invalid) value in Amount.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nerror about invalid amount, cannot send `/request`\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n![invalid](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/43258471-9a84fe18-90db-11e8-956a-132021c246c2.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Start 1-1 chat\r\n- in 1-1 chat send command with invalid amount, i.e. `/request ETH 0,1Aaa`\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: nightly 26/07/2018 0.9.24 (6255) \r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n* TF session: https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8537431/sessions/4397158307/?accessToken=6ZX1CN5kaexvsoBOsBbnFwNrHQ4\r\n\r\n\r\n",
